      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "### 🔋 How to read — Electrical\n**Battery, engine OFF:** 12.4–12.7 V good · <12.2 weak · <12.0 replace soon. &nbsp; **Engine RUNNING:** should sit **13.5–14.7 V** (alternator charging).\n\n🚩 Running voltage stuck **<13.0 V** = charging/alternator fault. 🚩 Resting voltage sagging lower month-after-month = battery dying (auto stop/start is hard on it)."
      },
      "transparent": false
    },
    {
      "id": 1,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Battery voltage",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 10,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 4
      },
      "datasource": {
        "type": "postgres",
        "uid": "project300k"
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": {
            "type": "postgres",
            "uid": "project300k"
          },
          "rawSql": "SELECT timestamp AS time, battery_v FROM electrical WHERE $__timeFilter(timestamp) ORDER BY timestamp",
          "format": "time_series"
